                <head>For the Spectator</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer>"Au Revoir"</trailer>
                <names/>
                <summary>Author details the sites of his trip by railroad across Virginia from
                    Staunton to Weston.</summary>
                <note/>
            </div>
            <pageNote>Most of page is poetry, literary and morality tales, etc. Column 5 has a note
                indicating that Senator Joshua R. Giddings of Ohio, has quit public life and gone to
                raise hemp in Ohio. Spectator believes it would be more appropriate "if the hemp
                would raise him." Bottom right of page is illegible.</pageNote>
        </page>
        <page n="02" image="va.au.ss.1860.07.10.02">
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>Is the Object Disunion?</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Spectator speculates that the ultimate aim of the Southern Democrats may be
                    secession and the breakup of the Union. Argues that a vote for the Bell/Everett
                    ticket would be the only way to defeat disunionists in the South and Republicans
                    in the North.</summary>
                <note/>
            </div>
