                <summary>Report of an exhibition of a new gun, named the "Virginia Pacificator." The
                    exhibition was put on by Lorenzo Sibert and J. Marshall McCue of Mt. Solon.
                    William Shaffer, a gunsmith from North River Gap in Mt. Solon, executed the
                    work. The gun can fire 49 times without reloading.</summary>
