                <summary>Report of the arrival of Governor Letcher and Joseph Mayo, Mayor of
                    Richmond, to Staunton and of the reception they received from the local military
                    companies. The companies were presented to the guests by Major General Harper
                    and General Harman. The Spectator then excepts the remainder of the story from
                    the Vindicator, which reports that the Governor and a number of citizens
                    proceeded to the house of Lieut. T.L. Harman and Capt. W.S.H. Baylor.</summary>
